list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: I think this is finished. Tests have to be done. A lot of them, but I don't know if I will be able to in time. We'll see.

task.summary: Default task
Some stuff related to graft, cast is maybe not the best choice, but ok
Made a HopMessage to count hops in the tree overlay
Changed dynamics of the lazy push to support piggybacking, and more
In process of transforming the entire way of communication between layers, hope it doesn't break anything. Introduced TCP!
Some interface changes, naming and organization, its WIP to get TCP to work, and to make the notification queue system work too
XBot TCP mostly done but not tested, still gonna do everything else of TCP
Nothing tested, but everything remodeled, a big big update. Should have done it in smaller increments but whateveeer
Small bug fix on Plumbot instance creation
Fixed bug where I was blocking the main Thread (App)
Fixed bug where TCP layer wasn't accepting new connections (nothing happened obviously)
Code is ugly. Fixed bug where I forgot to add OP_READ to newly accepted socket, and blocking to false.
Things about connections and channels have to be fixed. Later...
Small rollback
Broke everything, and don't know how to fix, but know I'm on the right track. I need to make sure the TCP connections are being opened and the upper layers (protocols) are aware of them.
A bit closer, but have to look more into the join/accept mechanism
Think I found solution: exchange IDs on connection so that the upper layers don't have to know specific ports, but only the id of the peer
On my way to implement that, just organized code a bit
Almost worked, but some things are still bugged :(
Added leave functionality. Gonna work on stabilizing network for Plumtree
Introduced the Tree check for optimizations. I think if TCP works, this is done, and it's all bug fixing. Need to run tests still.
Huge remake of the XBot class. Divided the 4 "states" of the XBot layer into 4 classes, so their behaviour is easier to understand, predict and code.
Still remaking, still haven't tested anything
More remake, on my way to make this a bit better I think, and easier to debug. Still left: waiting for and reacting to TCP connections
A lot more stuff made, nothing tested, as usual... sorry, myself from the future
I think this is finished. Tests have to be done. A lot of them, but I don't know if I will be able to in time. We'll see.
Started a whole new Refactor, trying to make everything simpler and the code more manageable
